  <div class="script-box">
    <span class="direction">[On location — standing at the edge of a pond, tools visible in the background]</span>
    <p>"Last episode I was in the greenhouse… getting my hands dirty with aquatic plants."</p>
    <p><em>(Small smile)</em><br>"Today… it's a little different."</p>
    <p>"Because today we're talking about pond service and maintenance — and honestly, this is one of those things that I think a lot of pond owners either don't know how to do… or just kind of hope they don't have to think about."</p>
    <p><em>(Beat)</em><br>"But the truth is… a pond that isn't maintained isn't really a pond. It's just… a really expensive puddle waiting to go wrong."</p>
    <p><em>(Slight laugh)</em><br>"And I'll be honest — even as someone who designs these things… there's a lot about what goes into keeping one healthy that I'm still learning."</p>
    <p>"So today, I'm getting out from behind the desk again — and we're going to figure this out together."</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section-label">Voiceover — B-Roll</div>
  <div class="script-box">
    <span class="direction">[B-roll: pond surface, filter systems, test kits, pump, algae close-ups]</span>
    <p>"A healthy pond is a balancing act. Water quality, filtration, algae, aeration — every single element affects the others. Get one thing wrong, and you can feel it ripple through the whole system."</p>
    <p>"And for the fish living in it… this isn't just aesthetics. It's life support."</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section-label">Transition Back On Camera</div>
  <div class="script-box">
    <p>"When most people think about pond maintenance… they think about maybe skimming some leaves off the top."</p>
    <p><em>(Small beat)</em><br>"And while that's… technically part of it… there is so much more happening beneath the surface."</p>
    <p>"So today we're going to break it all down — water testing, filtration, algae, water changes — the whole thing."</p>
    <p>"Let's get into it."</p>
  </div>

